==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Camphine
<hw>Cam*phine"</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧m*f⟦emac⟧n" <it>or</it>
k⟦acr⟧m"f⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Camphor</er>.]</ety>
<def>Rectified oil of turpentine, used for burning in lamps, and as a
common solvent in varnishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is also applied to a mixture of this substance
with three times its volume of alcohol and sometimes a little ether,
used as an illuminant.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Camphire</ent>⟦br⟧
